When shooting sunsets, dynamic range becomes an issue. The sky is either blown out, or the landscape is underexposed. The solution is combining multiple exposures into one shot. Using coordinates as programed key frames, a shot can be replicated several times with different exposures. You are able to achieve the HDR look even with a moving video.
